##### Vagrant Commands #####

vagrant init bento/ubuntu-16.04; vagrant up --provider virtualbox	start a new Vagrant VM with Ubuntu 16.04
vagrant ssh								ssh into default Vagrant VM
vagrant halt								gracefully shutdown VMi
vagrant up								restart the VM that is in that directory
vagrant status								shows the status of the VM in that directory
vagrant reload								bounce the VM
vagrant suspend								suspend the VM (not fully off)
vagrant resume								resume from suspended
vagrant destroy								destroy everything but shared folder (not shutdown)

